      "id": "q2",
      "question": "Does crypto.randomUUID() work in the jsdom test environment, or does it need a mock/polyfill?",
      "category": "codebase",
      "why_it_matters": "handleSubmitEdit calls crypto.randomUUID() for idempotencyKey. If jsdom doesn't provide it, edit-submission tests will throw at runtime."
    },
    {
      "id": "q3",
      "question": "Should the edit flow tests verify the exact mutation payload shape (accountId, variableId, target, context, session), or just verify mutation.mutate was called?",
      "category": "requirements",
      "why_it_matters": "The mutation payload includes conditional logic (isTargetMarket determines which variableId is used) and the context from useAssumptions. Testing payload shape catches regressions in that logic but couples the test to implementation details."
